ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Have you felt unusually tired or fatigued in the last week?
Please rate your fatigue (weariness, tiredness) by clicking on the button that best describes your fatigue RIGHT NOW.
Notes: 0=No Fatigue; 10=As bad as you can imagine

ElementDescription: Please rate your fatigue (weariness, tiredness) by clicking on the button that best describes your usual level of fatigue during the last 24 hours.
Notes: 0=No Fatigue; 10=As bad as you can imagine

ElementDescription: Please rate your fatigue (weariness, tiredness) by clicking on the button that best describes your WORST level of fatigue during the past 24 hours.
Notes: 0=No Fatigue; 10=As bad as you can imagine

ElementDescription: Describe during the past 24 hours, how much fatigue has interfered with your general activity
Describe during the past 24 hours, how much fatigue has interfered with your mood
Describe during the past 24 hours, how much fatigue has interfered with your walking ability
Describe during the past 24 hours, how much fatigue has interfered with your normal work (including work outside the home and chores)
Describe during the past 24 hours, how much fatigue has interfered with your relations with other people
Describe during the past 24 hours, how much fatigue has interfered with your enjoyment of life
